This paper is about improving the diversity and quality of machine translation using a novel sequence to sequence mixture model. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and training of specialized translation models, which are common topics in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of soft clustering, which is a technique commonly used in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of image captioning as a potential application, which falls under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
